# General Guidelines

- Never use the em dash "—". Use plain dash "-" instead.
- Never auto-add your agent name as a commit co-author.
- Never modify CHANGELOG.md or any file marked auto-generated.
- When writing or substantially editing long Markdown, put each full sentence on its own line. Preserve normal structure, but avoid wrapping multiple sentences onto one physical line.
- On technical decisions, give little weight to development cost. Prefer quality, simplicity, robustness, scalability, and long-term maintainability.
- Bug fixes: start by reproducing the bug in an E2E setting close to real usage, so the fix solves the real problem.
- UI/E2E work: be picky, obsess over pixel perfection. Fix obvious breakage even if it is not your task. Apply the same standard to lint, test failures, and flakiness.

---

# Communication

Default: **caveman full**. Revert: "normal mode" or "stop caveman". Switch: `/caveman lite|full|ultra`.
Drop caveman for: security warnings, irreversible action confirmations, ambiguous multi-step sequences.
Pushback: hold position when evidence supports it. No capitulation without cause.

